		How to maintain fml CVS tree

				Ken'ichi Fukamachi
				<fukachan@fml.org>

-----------------------------------------------------------------
* Firstly cvs checkout

0.	checkout fml repository

	% cvs co fml
	% cd fml

1.	set up TCP/IP to the Internet if needed.

2.	generate pkgsrc/

	% make pkgsrc

3.	set up $FML/.info and make documents

	% touch .info	(or get the latest .info)
	% make plaindoc
	% make htmldoc

4.	O.K. start your hack!


-----------------------------------------------------------------
* maintainer should check the version number

0.	check conf/release which is the main trunk version.

1.	define the current snapshot number conf/release_version.
